Q.Now how long did that continue - A.It has continued ever since, down to the prisoner's apprehension. After a time I asked him particular to the drawer;
James Edmonds
; whether he was not a young lad; in his house; he assured the he was not. I do not know any further conversation that went on about it; we certainly have had conversation about it; he always assured that he was a young man, a friend of his, that he would be always ready to serve him; but he never would let me see him.
